<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <title>About - Daily Mood </title>
    <style>
    body {
        background: #d4eaff !important;
        min-height: 100vh;
        padding-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    table, tbody, tr, td, th, .table, .table-striped tbody tr, .table-hover tbody tr:hover {
        background-color: transparent !important;
    }
    .container, .container-fluid {
        background-color: transparent !important;
    }
    
</style>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/navbar.ejs') %>
    <div class="container mt-3">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-8">
                <h2>About Daily Mood Journal</h2>
                <hr>
                
                <h5>Project Background</h5>
                <p>Daily Mood Journal is a simple personal mood tracking tool that helps you record your daily emotions.</p>
                
                <h5>Features</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li> Add new mood records ✔</li>
                    <li> View all mood entries ✔</li>
                    <li> Edit existing records ✔</li>
                    <li> View detailed information ✔</li>
                    <li> Delete records ✔</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h5>Technology Stack</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Node.js</strong> + <strong>Express</strong> - Backend framework</li>
                    <li><strong>EJS</strong> - Template engine</li>
                    <li><strong>Bootstrap 5</strong> - Frontend styling</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h5>Data Storage</h5>
                <p>Data is stored using <strong>in-memory array</strong> (no database). Data will reset when the server restarts.</p>
                
                <h5>Course Information</h5>
                <p>C237 Software Application Development - CA1 Project Mingke</p>
                
                <hr>
                <a href="/" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Back to Home</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <%- include('partials/footer.ejs') %>
</body>
</html>